To validate my AI‑Native Data Quality Agent, I built a synthetic e‑commerce order generator that simulates real‑world data evolution and data quality failures.

The generator produces six monthly batches of data, and each batch intentionally evolves in schema and quality to mimic real upstream changes.

At the core is _base_order, which creates a clean, realistic order record — order date, product, pricing, status, payment method, and customer info. It also models schema drift: batches 1–2 use a single state column, while batches 3+ split into shipping_state and billing_state, and batch 5 introduces a new discount_pct field. This mirrors how real systems evolve over time.”

