“generate_batch orchestrates the pipeline — base record → nulls → invalids → duplicates — and returns a DataFrame. generate_all_batches loops through each month, writes the batch to disk, and creates a realistic dataset with evolving schema and quality.

This dataset is what I use to test my PySpark DQ metrics pipeline and the LLM‑based anomaly explanation layer. It gives me full control over ground truth, drift, and failure modes, which is critical for validating an AI‑driven data quality system.
